[30;1m6 | [0m[35mmanupulation. You can use a|b (or) and a+b (and) operators. Expressions are[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35moptimized during the construction: merge ranges, simplify repetitions, etc.  It[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35malso contains a class for pattern matching allowing to search multiple strings[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mand regex at the same time.[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mRegex examples[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m==============[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1025[0m[34m of [0m[33m1051[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m201 | [0m[35mPatternMaching class[0m
[30;1m202 | [0m[35m====================[0m
[30;1m203 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m204 | [0m[35mUse PatternMaching if you would like to find many strings or regex in a string.[0m
[30;1m205 | [0m[35mUse addString() and addRegex() to add your patterns::[0m
[30;1m206 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m207 | [0m[35m    >>> from hachoir.regex import PatternMatching[0m
